1
00:00:51,370 --> 00:00:54,230
Yeong Rye, your boyfriend is here.

2
00:01:02,780 --> 00:01:05,730
He's not my boyfriend. He's just a friend.

3
00:01:07,590 --> 00:01:09,620
Come here. Sit over here.

4
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:25,420
If your night duty is over,
you should sleep at home.

5
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,890
Did you sleep in the night duty room?

6
00:01:26,890 --> 00:01:30,560
I didn't have the energy to go home.
I was passed out like a corpse.

7
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:33,790
I don't even remember the last time I was off.

8
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:36,080
You were off last Monday.

9
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:39,640
So, it's precisely your third day
off in eight days.

10
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,250
Is that right?

11
00:01:42,070 --> 00:01:46,470
Wow, and this is what I'm doing
on such a valuable day off.

12
00:01:46,470 --> 00:01:47,800
I didn't ask you to come.

13
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:51,030
Yeah, I came because I wanted to. Happy?

14
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,190
See?

15
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:03,480
If those two aren't together, I'd eat my hat.

16
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,600
And the fact that he comes here
to get his haircut by her.

17
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,870
How could a man and a woman be friends?

18
00:02:08,870 --> 00:02:10,200
I know.

19
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,740
But she says no.

20
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:15,040
Even though her eyes are dripping with honey.

21
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,650
Girls.

22
00:02:16,650 --> 00:02:20,410
Wash the towels instead of talking
about someone behind her back.

23
00:02:20,410 --> 00:02:23,760
The towels have a terrible stench.

24
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,950
Wash them thoroughly.

25
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:27,890
Okay, will do.

26
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:33,420
My gosh, they love to gossip.

27
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:39,130
It's okay. Go ahead.

28
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:47,900
Done.

29
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:52,360
Whoa...

30
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:55,800
I'm handsome as is. I look even better. Thank you.

31
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:59,060
Hey, I'll just shave your head.

32
00:02:59,060 --> 00:03:01,520
Thank you. Please control yourself, ma'am.

33
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,620
What time do you get off?

34
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:07,290
Around 8:30, after I clean up everything.

35
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:09,720
Then, I'll come and pick you up.

36
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:11,780
You told your mother that you'll be late, right?

37
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:13,040
Yeah.

38
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:16,710
[Yeongeun Market]

39
00:03:24,450 --> 00:03:26,850
Ho Suk, set the fresh kimchi aside.

40
00:03:26,850 --> 00:03:29,420
Aigoo, so crowded.

41
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,460
A table for you later.

42
00:03:32,460 --> 00:03:34,570
Yeah, got it.

43
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:37,680
Gosh, did you get a perm?

44
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,200
Yeah.

45
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,660
It'll last longer than a year.

46
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:43,350
- It will look nice, right?
- Yes, I think so.

47
00:03:44,470 --> 00:03:46,500
Why didn't you order baekban* today?
(White rice and side dishes)

48
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,110
I said you're dead if you betray me.

49
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:50,720
- I won't. Why would I betray you?
- Seriously.

50
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:53,950
Hey, your food is here.

51
00:03:53,950 --> 00:03:57,620
Aigoo, eat and work.

52
00:03:59,350 --> 00:04:00,700
Huh?

53
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:04,330
How is it?

54
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:06,620
Boil it for four more minutes on medium heat.

55
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:09,370
Got it. Okay...

56
00:04:12,590 --> 00:04:16,880
So, you ended up getting it from Oepo-ri.

57
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,600
It's way savorier this way.

58
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,370
Nothing gets past you, huh? Seriously.

59
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:25,760
Damn it. Look at the time.

60
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,160
Give me your phone.

61
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:35,510
[Menu]

62
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:37,020
[Phone Book]

63
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:38,320
[We sanitize the entire kitchen]

64
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:47,530
It's hot. Careful.

65
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:50,510
[Dumpling soup / Dumpling hotpot / May]

66
00:04:51,210 --> 00:04:53,220
Enjoy.

67
00:04:56,770 --> 00:04:58,740
Welcome! How many people?

68
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:00,360
Seven.

69
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,640
Come over here.

70
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,760
I'll clean up real quick.

71
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:07,090
Just a moment.

72
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:10,690
This is Yeong Sik's Baekban.

73
00:05:10,690 --> 00:05:13,820
Ho Suk, go pick up Su Jin now.

74
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:15,190
Su Jin?

75
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:18,870
I don't think I can because we have a big party.

76
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:22,700
Huh? Wait. I think I can.

77
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:26,030
Stop, stop! Oppa!

78
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:27,850
Oppa!

79
00:05:29,210 --> 00:05:31,700
Mr. Ma!

80
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:38,550
[Love and Jeotgal* for You]
(Salted seafood)

81
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:52,340
What? What? Why are you calling for Mr. Ma?

82
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,630
Are you busy right now?

83
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:54,820
Of course, I am.

84
00:05:54,820 --> 00:05:56,750
I need to stop by a shop, and there's
a Merchants' Association meeting.

85
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,840
I'm super busy. What is it?

86
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:02,670
I was going to ask you to pick up Su Jin
if you weren't busy.

87
00:06:02,670 --> 00:06:04,660
Su Jin?

88
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:09,740
[Sunny Kindergarten]

89
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:18,730
Su Jin, your mom is working today, right?

90
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:21,450
I think your grandma will come, then.

91
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:37,250
Gosh, hello.

92
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:39,140
Hello.

93
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:43,970
Have you been well?

94
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:45,940
Did you listen to the teacher?

95
00:06:47,090 --> 00:06:48,310
[Yeongeun Market]

96
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:57,730
[Yeong Sik's Baekban]

97
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:06,780
Here, here.

98
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:16,150
Here it is. Rolled omelet, Su Jin's favorite.

99
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,550
Here's the rolled omelet.

100
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:23,960
It's so fascinating to see her eating

101
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,880
with her tiny mouth.

102
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:30,540
You're such a good eater, Su Jin.

103
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:34,560
- Huh?
- Why not...

104
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,270
You don't want it?

105
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,040
Say ah.

106
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,680
My goodness!

107
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,610
- Oh, my gosh.
- Geez.

108
00:07:43,610 --> 00:07:46,110
Su Jin, I'm so sad.

109
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:50,420
Wow. This tiny girl already picks and
chooses who she likes.

110
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:52,490
You're so particular. Seriously.

111
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:55,180
Su Jin isn't being picky.

112
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:57,300
She just likes me.

113
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:01,370
- Right, Su Jin?
- Yes.

114
00:08:01,370 --> 00:08:03,810
I'm back.

115
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:05,830
- Mom is here.
- Hey, welcome back.

116
00:08:05,830 --> 00:08:07,700
Mom.

117
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:11,860
Yes, yes. My puppy. Were you eating?

118
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:15,030
My gosh. Even the fancy rolled omelet?

119
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:17,890
Did you thank Grandma?

120
00:08:17,890 --> 00:08:21,270
- Thank you, Grandma.
- Gosh.

121
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:23,010
You're welcome.

122
00:08:23,010 --> 00:08:24,340
You haven't had dinner, right?

123
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:26,510
Sit here. I'll get you a bowl of rice.

124
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:28,180
Pile it up high, ma'am.

125
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:29,640
I didn't even get to have lunch.

126
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:36,090
I almost went crazy today because
I missed you so much.

127
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:38,300
My baby. Sweetheart.

128
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:41,750
Hey, hey! Seriously.

129
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:46,020
Don't rub the lipstick on her delicate cheek.

130
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:47,540
Why do you care?

131
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:51,090
Whether I suck on my baby's
cheek or tap her little tush,

132
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:52,960
why do you care?

133
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:56,360
When you got drunk at a staff dinner last time,

134
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:59,700
you kissed her face so much that
she got bumps the next day.

135
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:02,990
I was so upset because of that.

136
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:06,450
Let me see, Su Jin.

137
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:08,680
Here. Here.

138
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,750
My gosh. Okay.

139
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,270
Yes, yes.

140
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:18,030
Gosh, so cute!

141
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:20,170
Whose baby are you?

142
00:09:20,170 --> 00:09:21,400
Your baby.

143
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:25,360
Aigoo, yes. You're so smart. Gosh.

144
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,070
I gave birth to her.

145
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:30,580
Why do you keep calling her your baby? Geez.

146
00:09:30,580 --> 00:09:33,760
By the way, why didn't you come with Yeong Rye?

147
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:37,970
[Jullee Beauty Salon]

148
00:09:37,970 --> 00:09:40,300
- Did you wait long?
- No.

149
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:42,090
Let's go.

150
00:09:42,090 --> 00:09:45,400
By the way, I'm a bit hungry.

151
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,730
My stomach keeps growling.

152
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:50,210
Is it?

153
00:09:50,210 --> 00:09:51,870
- Let me hear it.
- Hey.

154
00:09:52,740 --> 00:09:55,310
Your stomach knows exactly what time it is.

155
00:09:55,310 --> 00:09:58,340
It asks for food when it's time. Wow, so accurate.

156
00:09:58,340 --> 00:10:00,790
Let's eat something. It's my treat.

157
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:03,920
Like you weren't going to pay?

158
00:10:06,330 --> 00:10:07,730
Geez.

159
00:10:09,490 --> 00:10:10,820
Let's go.

160
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:16,740
[Episode 7: Fate]

161
00:10:16,740 --> 00:10:20,830
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

162
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:23,190
♪ Happy birthday, dear Ga Ryeong ♪

163
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:25,420
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

164
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:28,050
- Blow it out. Blow it out.
- Make a wish.

165
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,420
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

166
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:35,680
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

167
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:39,530
♪ Happy birthday, dear Jong Hui ♪

168
00:10:39,530 --> 00:10:43,520
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

169
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,370
- Blow it out. Blow it out.
- Hold on. Hold on.

170
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:47,880
Make a wish. A wish.

171
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,940
Happy birthday!

172
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:03,230
Happy birthday.

173
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:04,520
We prepared this together.

174
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,810
- Thank you.
- Here it is.

175
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,570
What do you think?

176
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:11,950
Try this hamburger, too.

177
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:14,230
Isn't it good?

178
00:11:14,230 --> 00:11:15,730
- My treat.
- Really?

179
00:11:15,730 --> 00:11:17,900
Eat a lot.

180
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:21,720
I'll put it together.

181
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:24,320
Let's see how the hamburgers are.

182
00:11:26,540 --> 00:11:27,790
It's tasty.

183
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:30,040
I feel alive now.

184
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:38,550
Geez...

185
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:42,710
Thank you.

186
00:11:45,770 --> 00:11:49,060
Hold on. You can't just drink it.

187
00:11:49,060 --> 00:11:51,620
You want to bet on who drinks faster?

188
00:11:51,620 --> 00:11:55,350
Okay. I know how to drink a soda.

189
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:58,880
Whoever loses will carry this until the end. Deal?

190
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,170
Deal.

191
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:02,930
Start.

192
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:13,500
Okay! I win.

193
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,770
Okay, okay! I win. See?

194
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:19,570
Gosh, sorry.

195
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:24,270
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

196
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,290
- Give me.
- It's okay. I'll carry it.

197
00:12:28,290 --> 00:12:30,380
No, let me.

198
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,320
Would you like some water, Father?

199
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,950
No. It will make me feel full.

200
00:12:58,950 --> 00:13:00,130
How about a beverage, then?

201
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:03,240
Beverages are water, too.

202
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,020
Don't make me repeat myself.

203
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:09,600
Anyway, it feels too stuffy in here.

204
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:14,670
I'm always lying down in the white hospital room.

205
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:17,910
Get me discharged. Do it.

206
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:22,340
I said we can't relax just yet.

207
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:26,000
What if something happens
while you're home alone?

208
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:28,300
- I know it feels stuffy-
- Have you been in my shoes?

209
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:31,000
Have you been hospitalized for a long time?

210
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:34,670
- Father, please.
- Ahjussi...

211
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,300
Here. Should I cut your hair shorter?

212
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,740
I think I could, since you have
a nicely shaped head.

213
00:13:42,830 --> 00:13:45,710
No. I should stop for the day.

214
00:13:45,710 --> 00:13:48,590
So, I could visit you again. Right?

215
00:13:48,590 --> 00:13:51,350
Why bother keep visiting an old, sick man?

216
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,720
Why not? I'd like to.

217
00:13:57,100 --> 00:14:00,200
Okay, Ahjussi. Try this.

218
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:03,000
It has a lot of vitamin C
since it's real fruit juice.

219
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,020
It's nice and tangy, too. Here.

220
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:07,310
Here.

221
00:14:07,310 --> 00:14:09,330
I said I'm full.

222
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,670
It doesn't taste too bad.

223
00:14:26,950 --> 00:14:30,050
- I'm here.
- You came.

224
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:31,630
You're here, Yeong Rye.

225
00:14:31,630 --> 00:14:36,070
Gosh, why do you look prettier
each time I see you?

226
00:14:36,070 --> 00:14:38,950
Gosh. These women.

227
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:41,680
They asked all sorts of
questions as if they'd buy.

228
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,460
But they said they'll buy later.

229
00:14:43,460 --> 00:14:45,270
They took a bunch of samples.

230
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:47,950
Seriously. Those jerks.

231
00:14:47,950 --> 00:14:49,360
Has Father eaten?

232
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:51,520
He finished the porridge.

233
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,380
Yeong Rye used her skills again.

234
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:56,150
Really? Of course.

235
00:14:56,150 --> 00:15:00,090
That picky man does everything Yeong Rye says.

236
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:03,610
You must want to rest since
you worked all day. I'm sorry.

237
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:07,290
It's okay. I do this because I like it.

238
00:15:07,290 --> 00:15:09,120
He's in your care.

239
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:12,550
He has gotten so stubborn since he's been sick.

240
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:14,700
He doesn't like the barbershop at the hospital.

241
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:17,270
He doesn't like the volunteer
hairdressers, either.

242
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:22,300
If it weren't for you, he would look
like a beggar from Cheonggyecheon.

243
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:26,500
- His hair was-
- Hey, hey. Stop being silly.

244
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:36,290
Ahjussi, I'll dye your hair next time.

245
00:15:36,290 --> 00:15:38,740
You'll look 10 years younger.

246
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:41,400
But you need to get rehabilitation.

247
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:45,370
You look much better than the last time I saw you.

248
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:48,620
Okay. Go now.

249
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:51,600
- You need to go to work tomorrow, too.
- Yes.

250
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:54,190
- I'll get going, Ahjumma.
- Okay, okay.

251
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:56,470
- Take care.
- Okay.

252
00:15:57,910 --> 00:15:59,350
- I'll see her off.
- Okay.

253
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:01,940
Yes, Yeong Rye. Thank you. Bye.

254
00:16:06,070 --> 00:16:09,630
How long will you leave Yeong Rye like that?

255
00:16:09,630 --> 00:16:12,900
I told you to make a move
before someone else does.

256
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:14,850
Geez. Here we go again.

257
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:17,420
Don't just dismiss me like that.

258
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:21,400
She's pretty, but also sweet.
You think that's common?

259
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:24,720
Don't regret it later. Hold onto her, you stupid-

260
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:27,130
Gosh. That little...

261
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:31,150
Gosh, so frustrating.

262
00:16:37,190 --> 00:16:41,280
She's pretty, but also sweet.
You think that's common?

263
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:44,930
Don't regret it later. Hold onto her, you stupid-

264
00:16:46,330 --> 00:16:48,100
Huh?

265
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,510
Huh?

266
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:51,420
What?

267
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:55,060
Are you trying to pick a fight?
Why glance at me like that?

268
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:57,490
What? What is it? What is it?

269
00:16:58,370 --> 00:17:02,560
Well, I thought you must be tired.

270
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:05,130
Your eyes are red.

271
00:17:05,130 --> 00:17:08,870
R-Really? I look terrible, huh?

272
00:17:10,670 --> 00:17:12,010
Hold on.

273
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:20,400
How's that? You feel better, right?

274
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:24,230
Yes. I guess I do.

275
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:25,340
Do that on your way home.

276
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:28,190
- A warm compress will be good.
- Okay.

277
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:30,450
Code Blue. Code Blue.

278
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:31,860
Don't you have to go?

279
00:17:31,860 --> 00:17:34,600
I do. Don't take the bus. Take a taxi.

280
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,440
Okay. Get going.

281
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:39,010
Take a taxi. I'll check later.

282
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,600
Come.

283
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:48,900
It's chilly since it just rained.

284
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:52,580
Wrap yourself up since it's cold.

285
00:17:55,490 --> 00:17:56,900
Bye.

286
00:18:12,370 --> 00:18:13,920
I thought you were off today.

287
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:16,390
I know. I'm so blessed with work.

288
00:18:16,390 --> 00:18:17,820
Let's go.

289
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,480
[Yeong Sik's Baekban]

290
00:18:28,370 --> 00:18:30,600
I'm back.

291
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:33,050
Gosh, why do you look like that?

292
00:18:33,050 --> 00:18:37,170
I know. Someone made me look like this.

293
00:18:37,170 --> 00:18:38,160
Where's everyone?

294
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:40,170
I made them go upstairs.

295
00:18:40,170 --> 00:18:42,080
They kept chatting next to me.

296
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:45,700
They aren't helpful, but they are so noisy.

297
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:49,010
I guess my life wasn't supposed to be easy.

298
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:52,640
More people to take care of on top
of my family. So bothersome.

299
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:56,590
You say that, but you care about them the most.

300
00:18:56,590 --> 00:19:00,560
Your words and feelings don't match at all.

301
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:02,010
Hey, shut up.

302
00:19:02,010 --> 00:19:04,010
Have you been inside my heart?

303
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:07,470
I have. I came from you.

304
00:19:08,770 --> 00:19:12,100
So, how's that old man doing?

305
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,740
- Jae Pil's father?
- Yes.

306
00:19:14,740 --> 00:19:16,920
He's the same, you know.

307
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:22,170
Geez. They say no flower lasts forever.

308
00:19:22,170 --> 00:19:25,070
Old sayings are never wrong.

309
00:19:25,070 --> 00:19:29,390
He probably didn't know when
he was all high and mighty.

310
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:33,030
His department store failed overnight

311
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:35,900
and he passed out from the shock.

312
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:38,700
But despite the struggles,

313
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:41,370
that woman, Man Ok, is so loyal

314
00:19:41,370 --> 00:19:43,530
and she sells door-to-door and cares for him.

315
00:19:43,530 --> 00:19:47,250
They're hanging in there since
her son became an intern.

316
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:50,500
You could write Jae Pil's father's biography.

317
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:53,780
How do you know his family history so well?

318
00:19:53,780 --> 00:19:56,060
I heard about it too many times. That's why.

319
00:19:56,060 --> 00:19:58,630
Man Ok tells me all the time, you know.

320
00:19:58,630 --> 00:20:02,470
Write a biography? Seriously.

321
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,380
Hey, sister.

322
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:43,150
It's late. Don't you think it's too loud?

323
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:44,850
Okay.

324
00:20:53,070 --> 00:20:55,580
Can you read in this noise?

325
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:56,880
Read downstairs.

326
00:20:56,880 --> 00:21:00,090
This is better. It's nice and cool.

327
00:21:00,090 --> 00:21:03,170
The room is too small and stuffy.

328
00:21:03,170 --> 00:21:04,710
I'm sorry.

329
00:21:04,710 --> 00:21:07,070
I'll make a lot of money

330
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:12,180
and get a house with your own room and a big yard.

331
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:19,970
I'm back.

332
00:21:19,970 --> 00:21:21,140
Auntie.

333
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:24,540
Gosh, my Su Jin. Were you having ice cream?

334
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:26,250
You're eating it with your nose and cheeks?

335
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,510
It must be delicious.

336
00:21:30,010 --> 00:21:31,950
You're home.

337
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:35,120
You aren't as late as usual tonight.

338
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,500
I thought you'd be back later.

339
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:41,860
Why? Is there a reason I shouldn't be home early?

340
00:21:43,790 --> 00:21:45,450
Geez. It smells.

341
00:21:45,450 --> 00:21:48,790
I told you to open the windows
when you grill dried fish.

342
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:54,570
Look at this. I knew it.

343
00:21:54,570 --> 00:21:56,890
Drink at home no more than twice a month.

344
00:21:56,890 --> 00:21:58,670
Did you forget our co-living rule?

345
00:21:58,670 --> 00:22:01,190
You have a child, but you always drink soju.

346
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:03,580
It can't be good for Su Jin.

347
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:07,040
Ho Suk, you're on laundry duty today.
Did you do the laundry?

348
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:10,870
What's piled up so high in the laundry hamper?

349
00:22:10,870 --> 00:22:12,700
Jeong Bun...

350
00:22:15,030 --> 00:22:18,420
You said you'll clean the fridge
at least two weeks ago.

351
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:22,480
Okay, fine, girl. I'll do it. I'll do.

352
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,370
I was going to do it, too.

353
00:22:24,370 --> 00:22:28,420
But Unni suggested drinking just one glass.

354
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:29,710
Do better.

355
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:33,450
I cleaned the bathroom before work today.

356
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:47,180
She's starting to resemble someone.

357
00:22:47,180 --> 00:22:51,430
I know. She's little Kwon Hae Ja. Seriously.

358
00:22:51,430 --> 00:22:53,120
Stop talking behind my back.

359
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,820
You little.

360
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:04,900
Is she sleeping?

361
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:06,260
She is.

362
00:23:13,690 --> 00:23:17,470
Is Mother using water downstairs? I didn't-

363
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:30,650
I'm sorry. Sorry, sorry.

364
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:34,950
She refuses to sleep these days.

365
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:40,680
I need to tell her a story a hundred
times to get her to sleep.

366
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,630
But she must've been tired today.

367
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:46,540
After one lullaby, she started snoring.

368
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:49,100
Mr. Ma played with her today.

369
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:51,140
How many times did he spin her around?

370
00:23:51,140 --> 00:23:54,020
Men sure are different.

371
00:23:54,020 --> 00:23:59,300
His arms must be pretty sore today.

372
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:04,100
It sure is reassuring to have Sang Cheol around.

373
00:24:07,420 --> 00:24:12,280
Hey, should we ask Mom to take care of Su Jin

374
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:14,940
and go to Dongdaemun tonight?

375
00:24:14,940 --> 00:24:17,750
- Should we?
- Let's go. Let's go.

376
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:19,330
Give me a discount.

377
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:23,040
Unni, Unni. Check this out. Isn't it pretty?

378
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:24,640
Have a look.

379
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,690
What do you think? You want this?

380
00:24:26,690 --> 00:24:27,840
I'm sorry. It's not my style.

381
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:30,300
I'll give a good deal. A discount.

382
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:32,700
- 20% off?
- Bye.

383
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:37,280
Do we get a discount, too?

384
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:40,790
Hey! What are you doing here without telling me?

385
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:43,680
Gosh, why are you so shocked?

386
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:46,100
Gosh. My goodness.

387
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:47,800
Who's here?

388
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:51,440
- Hey, Three Musketeers.
- Unni!

389
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:53,730
It's been so long.

390
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:56,820
You haven't been here since you came last fall.

391
00:24:56,820 --> 00:24:59,440
They've been busy making a living, too.

392
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:02,310
Right, Yeong Rye. Is the night
college prep going well?

393
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:04,020
I'm taking it in stride.

394
00:25:04,020 --> 00:25:06,190
But I'll try to enroll this year.

395
00:25:06,190 --> 00:25:09,940
What? Taking it in stride, my foot.
You have no idea.

396
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:12,180
She studies so hard every night.

397
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:15,790
She has a private room, and the rest
of us use the master bedroom.

398
00:25:15,790 --> 00:25:20,170
She doesn't sleep. She lost her mind.

399
00:25:20,170 --> 00:25:23,120
She's always been a hard worker.

400
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:26,320
She works during the day and studies at night.

401
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:28,540
She's burning the late-night oil.

402
00:25:28,540 --> 00:25:31,770
Unni, it's midnight oil, not late-night oil.

403
00:25:31,770 --> 00:25:33,960
Hey, it's the same thing.

404
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:36,970
Ass, arse. It's the same.

405
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:41,860
Gosh, this reminds me of the old days.

406
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:44,950
Hae Ja was a piece of work back then, wasn't she?

407
00:25:44,950 --> 00:25:45,980
I know.

408
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:48,760
She bossed around depending on how she felt.

409
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:52,180
And she got quiet after Seo Jong Hui came.

410
00:25:52,180 --> 00:25:54,920
So, what's she up to, by the way?

411
00:26:01,650 --> 00:26:05,440
I'm sure Jong Hui is doing well wherever she is.

412
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:08,770
I'm sure. Yes.

413
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:11,440
I gave you the drinks. Why won't
you drink it? Go ahead.

414
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:13,260
Thank you.

415
00:26:23,900 --> 00:26:26,900
[Yeong Sik's Baekban]

416
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,510
Here. Take the soups.

417
00:26:37,510 --> 00:26:39,860
Okay. Yeong Mi.

418
00:26:43,040 --> 00:26:44,880
Passing by.

419
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,790
It's hot. Be careful.

420
00:27:10,190 --> 00:27:11,530
Let's eat.

421
00:27:11,530 --> 00:27:14,370
Thank you for the meal.

422
00:27:17,860 --> 00:27:22,470
- Hey, do you have to go to work right away?
- Yes.

423
00:27:22,470 --> 00:27:25,800
Geez. We're getting cabbage later.

424
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:28,800
Ho Suk and I need to make fresh kimchi.

425
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,770
I don't think we have time
to drop off Su Jin today.

426
00:27:31,770 --> 00:27:34,890
Me, me. I'll do it. I'll drop her off.

427
00:27:34,890 --> 00:27:36,970
Gosh, what's gotten into you?

428
00:27:36,970 --> 00:27:41,070
Is she finally maturing since she's a year older?

429
00:27:41,070 --> 00:27:44,610
Of course. I'm a middle schooler now.

430
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,530
Eat this.

431
00:27:49,530 --> 00:27:52,430
Seriously.

432
00:27:52,430 --> 00:27:54,000
What a relief.

433
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,340
Bland is better than salty.

434
00:28:00,290 --> 00:28:04,560
Oh, my! Hey, what's this?

435
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:06,280
Rose Day?

436
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,390
There are all sorts of days.

437
00:28:08,390 --> 00:28:10,860
Valentine's Day. White Day.

438
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:13,550
It must be a day to confess your feelings, huh?

439
00:28:13,550 --> 00:28:15,560
It's another marketing ploy.

440
00:28:15,560 --> 00:28:18,730
People are so clever with stuff like this.

441
00:28:18,730 --> 00:28:20,360
Hey.

442
00:28:21,270 --> 00:28:27,210
Why don't you express your feelings to Jae Pil?

443
00:28:27,210 --> 00:28:31,560
The rose-shaped soaps are pretty, too.

444
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:34,580
[Orange roses - Shy first love]

445
00:28:34,580 --> 00:28:38,200
Jae Pil? Why suddenly bring him up?

446
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:41,390
Your relationship is so vague.

447
00:28:41,390 --> 00:28:45,250
The girls at the shop always argue about you two.

448
00:28:45,250 --> 00:28:48,020
Saying you're dating or not dating all the time.

449
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:52,020
Even I can tell you aren't just friends.

450
00:28:52,020 --> 00:28:53,810
Be honest with me.

451
00:28:53,810 --> 00:28:55,330
Do you like him or not?

452
00:28:55,330 --> 00:28:57,460
I know you do.

453
00:28:57,460 --> 00:28:59,450
We're running late. Hurry.

454
00:28:59,450 --> 00:29:02,130
Let bygones be bygones.

455
00:29:02,130 --> 00:29:04,440
You've spent so much time together. You could've-

456
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,810
The bus is here. Let's go.

457
00:29:05,810 --> 00:29:07,490
Hey, hey...

458
00:29:23,570 --> 00:29:30,430
Gosh. Why do rich people
build houses on the hills?

459
00:29:30,430 --> 00:29:35,380
They must be fine with it
since they get driven around.

460
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:43,230
If I become rich again, I'll build on flat land.

461
00:29:43,230 --> 00:29:45,140
Flat land.

462
00:29:46,340 --> 00:29:47,990
Here I am.

463
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:57,550
Who is it?

464
00:29:57,550 --> 00:30:01,470
Hello, it's Yudanhwa Cosmetics.

465
00:30:01,470 --> 00:30:02,930
[Yudanhwa Cosmetics]

466
00:30:07,070 --> 00:30:11,740
Gosh. Ma'am, you got melasma.

467
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:14,920
It was gone when you started
using our new product.

468
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,280
Really?

469
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:19,730
I went to Hawaii with my husband
for his business trip.

470
00:30:19,730 --> 00:30:21,340
Maybe the sun was too strong there.

471
00:30:21,340 --> 00:30:23,870
No wonder.

472
00:30:23,870 --> 00:30:28,290
We just released a melasma cream.

473
00:30:28,290 --> 00:30:30,920
It's amazingly effective.

474
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:33,730
You know Jeong Bo Ra, the celebrity, right?

475
00:30:33,730 --> 00:30:35,250
She's in her 50s,

476
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:38,140
but her melasma disappeared
since she started using it.

477
00:30:38,140 --> 00:30:39,330
Really?

478
00:30:39,330 --> 00:30:43,200
Her skin did look clear these days.

479
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:45,800
Right? You noticed it.

480
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,540
You're so observant.

481
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:50,160
But it doesn't just work on melasma-

482
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:53,230
Right. Jae Pil finished his program, right?

483
00:30:53,230 --> 00:30:54,660
Is he an intern now?

484
00:30:54,660 --> 00:30:56,580
Yes. He is.

485
00:30:56,580 --> 00:30:59,220
Time really flies.

486
00:30:59,220 --> 00:31:02,210
That means we age as quickly.

487
00:31:02,210 --> 00:31:05,100
We need to take care of ourselves. That cream-

488
00:31:05,100 --> 00:31:09,430
It's such a relief that he got
into medical school.

489
00:31:09,430 --> 00:31:11,720
It would've been so disappointing otherwise.

490
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:15,580
You never worked a day before,
but look at you now.

491
00:31:15,580 --> 00:31:18,230
Gosh. I feel bad.

492
00:31:18,230 --> 00:31:20,640
That's just my fate.

493
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:25,590
If you feel so bad, please buy the cream-

494
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:29,010
Hand me the phone, Honey.

495
00:31:29,010 --> 00:31:30,810
Okay.

496
00:31:30,810 --> 00:31:32,200
Goodness.

497
00:31:36,850 --> 00:31:38,320
Here.

498
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,610
Hello?

499
00:31:40,610 --> 00:31:44,470
Hyeon, it's Mom. Everything's okay, right?

500
00:31:45,300 --> 00:31:47,090
- Aigoo.
- Really?

501
00:31:47,090 --> 00:31:49,750
You're coming to Korea this weekend?

502
00:31:50,470 --> 00:31:51,920
My goodness.

503
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:55,320
Can't you tell? I'm thrilled, of course.

504
00:31:55,320 --> 00:31:57,960
Hold on. We need to redo the wallpaper

505
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:00,790
in your room and get a new bed, too.

506
00:32:00,790 --> 00:32:03,390
Yes. Okay, okay.

507
00:32:04,270 --> 00:32:08,330
Okay, I said. I'll take care of it.

508
00:32:08,330 --> 00:32:11,070
Okay. Call me later.

509
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,590
Your son is coming to Korea?

510
00:32:13,590 --> 00:32:14,890
Yes.

511
00:32:14,890 --> 00:32:16,510
I don't have time for this.

512
00:32:16,510 --> 00:32:19,820
I would've redone the wallpaper if I had known.

513
00:32:19,820 --> 00:32:22,350
What color should I choose?

514
00:32:22,350 --> 00:32:26,010
Wait, ma'am! The melasma cream...

515
00:32:26,010 --> 00:32:29,710
M-Melasma... Melasma...

516
00:32:32,860 --> 00:32:35,500
How dare you stare at me like that?

517
00:32:35,500 --> 00:32:37,910
Look down now.

518
00:32:37,910 --> 00:32:39,730
Why should I look down?

519
00:32:39,730 --> 00:32:42,250
My mom gave me these pretty eyes.

520
00:32:42,250 --> 00:32:43,910
You look down instead.

521
00:32:43,910 --> 00:32:48,000
Wow. You really are crazy.

522
00:32:48,790 --> 00:32:51,920
Hey, what makes you so confident?

523
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:55,140
I heard you disrupted our work yesterday.

524
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:56,620
Work, my foot.

525
00:32:56,620 --> 00:33:01,320
Hey. I know you're bad kids,
but try to be classier.

526
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:03,750
Aren't you embarrassed to mug kids?

527
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:06,840
You know you're making all the
bad kids look bad, right?

528
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:10,200
What? You think you could just say whatever?

529
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,370
What? Will you hit me?

530
00:33:12,370 --> 00:33:16,120
Then, you should move faster than just talking.

531
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:18,570
Hey! Let go!

532
00:33:18,570 --> 00:33:20,630
Let go! Let go!

533
00:33:20,630 --> 00:33:23,370
Hey, let go! Are you crazy?

534
00:33:23,370 --> 00:33:27,570
You crazy bitch! What are you doing? Let go!

535
00:33:27,570 --> 00:33:29,170
Yeong Bae.

536
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:31,320
[Ko Yeong Bae]

537
00:33:34,690 --> 00:33:35,920
[Han Se Ri]

538
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:42,840
Hey! How dare you? You little!

539
00:33:44,870 --> 00:33:46,950
Ko Yeong Bae.

540
00:33:46,950 --> 00:33:49,410
Wait for me.

541
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:54,640
Hey, I didn't start it.

542
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:59,140
They picked a fight with me
while I was waiting for you.

543
00:33:59,140 --> 00:34:01,970
Violence is not acceptable for any reason.

544
00:34:01,970 --> 00:34:04,750
They're the bitches.

545
00:34:04,750 --> 00:34:07,120
They mugged-

546
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:08,730
Speak nicely.

547
00:34:08,730 --> 00:34:11,510
They're bitches. I can't speak nicely about them.

548
00:34:11,510 --> 00:34:13,560
You always nag me.

549
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:15,340
Hey, my family business failed

550
00:34:15,340 --> 00:34:17,480
and my dad lives in the hospital
after he collapsed.

551
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:21,360
I have an excuse to act out, okay?

552
00:34:22,140 --> 00:34:25,730
Wait for me, I said. Ko Yeong Bae.

553
00:34:25,730 --> 00:34:27,940
So, I was kneeling and my knees-

554
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,030
I'm back.

555
00:34:29,030 --> 00:34:32,170
Hey, seriously. Listen to me.

556
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:35,380
Han Se Ri, why are you here
instead of going home?

557
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:37,820
No one's at home, anyway.

558
00:34:37,820 --> 00:34:40,430
I'll do homework with Yeong Bae.

559
00:34:40,430 --> 00:34:43,810
Hey! Don't distract Yeong Bae!

560
00:34:43,810 --> 00:34:45,200
- It's okay. It's okay.
- Gosh.

561
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:47,660
You'd better not run your mouth next to him.

562
00:34:47,660 --> 00:34:52,200
Gosh. Who does she take after to be so chatty?

563
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:55,300
Anyway, where was I?

564
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:57,710
- You sat on the marble floor, so-
- Yes, right.

565
00:34:57,710 --> 00:35:00,070
I was giving her a massage,

566
00:35:00,070 --> 00:35:03,640
and she kept hinting that she
might buy. Don't tease me, at least.

567
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:05,220
I have a son, too.

568
00:35:05,220 --> 00:35:08,120
She went upstairs in the middle of the massage.

569
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:11,200
Geez. What an annoying woman. She's so uppity.

570
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:14,200
She only talks as if she cares about me.

571
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:18,130
So, when is Jeong Hyeon coming?

572
00:35:18,130 --> 00:35:19,660
This weekend, I guess.

573
00:35:19,660 --> 00:35:22,440
Yeong Sik said he won't come until next year.

574
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:25,040
He must be coming all of a sudden.

575
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,600
I'd be happy if I were her, too.

576
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:30,460
He's their only child, you know.

577
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:32,440
What's this, Unni?

578
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:35,010
Are you defending her, not me?

579
00:35:35,010 --> 00:35:37,500
Because her son is Yeong Sik's friend?

580
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:40,570
I'm not taking sides. It's not
like I don't know them.

581
00:35:40,570 --> 00:35:43,180
Of course, you are.

582
00:35:43,180 --> 00:35:47,070
You know I'm insecure since
our business failed, right?

583
00:35:47,070 --> 00:35:50,920
I get disappointed over little things.

584
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:53,900
Come on. Be on my side. Come on.

585
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:56,240
Come on. Be on my side. Right now.

586
00:35:56,240 --> 00:36:00,360
Yes, you're right. Rich people are worse.

587
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:04,310
Buying a cream would be nothing to her.

588
00:36:04,310 --> 00:36:06,990
She should've bought it first
before taking care of her son.

589
00:36:06,990 --> 00:36:09,530
What a lousy woman.

590
00:36:09,530 --> 00:36:12,540
I hope she trips while walking.

591
00:36:15,240 --> 00:36:17,570
Are you happy?

592
00:36:17,570 --> 00:36:19,680
I am. I am.

593
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:22,010
Gosh, I'd rather die. Seriously.

594
00:36:22,010 --> 00:36:26,090
I must've sinned in my previous life.
How did we become friends?

595
00:36:26,090 --> 00:36:28,870
Gosh. I'm so sick of it.

596
00:36:28,870 --> 00:36:35,040
By the way, human connections are so funny.

597
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:38,380
Because Jeong Hyeon introduced Yeong Sik to us,

598
00:36:38,380 --> 00:36:40,570
Yeong Sik became Jae Pil's tutor.

599
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:44,150
And thanks to that, Jae Pil got
into medical school.

600
00:36:44,150 --> 00:36:49,080
He seems to be born to be a doctor, Unni.

601
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,900
Sunbae!

602
00:37:02,350 --> 00:37:03,420
Guys.

603
00:37:03,420 --> 00:37:05,580
What? Why are you freaking out now?

604
00:37:05,580 --> 00:37:07,250
Did the sky fall?

605
00:37:07,250 --> 00:37:09,910
Or did we get a ton of patients?

606
00:37:09,910 --> 00:37:12,510
No, it's not that.

607
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:16,410
You know the Medical Students' Night this week?

608
00:37:16,410 --> 00:37:17,510
Yes.

609
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:20,170
They charge you a huge fee if you
don't bring a date. Is that true?

610
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:23,310
I see. Chang Eui must be freaking out again.

611
00:37:23,310 --> 00:37:24,940
There weren't any fees, right?

612
00:37:24,940 --> 00:37:26,540
I know.

613
00:37:26,540 --> 00:37:31,160
I'm in trouble. I'm already running
low on money this month.

614
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,860
Good luck.

615
00:37:34,050 --> 00:37:35,410
Geez.

616
00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:44,170
- Eat.
- Okay.

617
00:37:49,170 --> 00:37:52,837
Han Jae Pil, you know that friend of yours?

618
00:37:52,837 --> 00:37:56,710
- Who?
- The one who comes to cut your father's hair.

619
00:37:57,630 --> 00:37:59,400
She's just a friend, right?

620
00:38:02,890 --> 00:38:05,990
Introduce me. She's totally my type.

621
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,270
I'll treat you generously if it works out.

622
00:38:09,270 --> 00:38:12,270
I'll get you beef, not pork. How does that sound?

623
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:14,780
I can't.

624
00:38:14,780 --> 00:38:16,720
Even tiger meat won't do.

625
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,990
Why? Why not?

626
00:38:18,990 --> 00:38:21,450
You said she's not your girlfriend.

627
00:38:24,090 --> 00:38:27,590
Don't just say no and tell me why.

628
00:38:34,470 --> 00:38:36,080
Anyway, I can't.

629
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:38,920
I don't want to.

630
00:39:03,430 --> 00:39:07,140
Gosh. No. Things would just get awkward.

631
00:39:20,620 --> 00:39:22,770
Wake up. Wake up.

632
00:39:22,770 --> 00:39:25,300
"Rose Day is just around the corner.

633
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:28,710
Would I be able to express my feelings this time?

634
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:33,080
I hope I'll be able to. Here's my song request."

635
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,680
Shin Jeong Hui from Hongje-dong
sent this message.

636
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:38,750
Here's her requested song.

637
00:39:38,750 --> 00:39:41,760
"Susanne" by Kim Seung Jin.

638
00:39:46,130 --> 00:39:48,690
Gosh. How amazing.

639
00:39:48,690 --> 00:39:52,510
How can someone have a voice like that?

640
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:55,830
Gosh, hot!

641
00:39:55,830 --> 00:39:59,840
Be careful. You're about to burn all of my hair.

642
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:02,900
Gosh. I told you to practice with a wig.

643
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:04,620
I'm so scared.

644
00:40:04,620 --> 00:40:07,340
Wigs are nothing like real hair.

645
00:40:07,340 --> 00:40:11,330
And I bought you that pastry for being my model.

646
00:40:11,330 --> 00:40:15,000
Sit still. Stop being annoying.

647
00:40:16,400 --> 00:40:17,630
I'm back.

648
00:40:17,630 --> 00:40:19,380
- Hey.
- Hey, Unni.

649
00:40:19,380 --> 00:40:21,530
I smell something burnt.

650
00:40:24,260 --> 00:40:27,530
I told you. You burned all of my hair.

651
00:40:27,530 --> 00:40:30,190
Gosh. You drive me crazy, Unni.

652
00:40:30,190 --> 00:40:32,010
It didn't burn. Not at all.

653
00:40:32,010 --> 00:40:33,960
It didn't burn at all. Look.

654
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:36,820
Smell it. It didn't. You look pretty
like Marie Antoinette.

655
00:40:36,820 --> 00:40:38,230
It smells like it burned.

656
00:40:38,230 --> 00:40:40,550
I swear it didn't burn.

657
00:40:40,550 --> 00:40:41,800
I'll answer it.

658
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:44,360
- Do a better job, okay?
- It didn't burn. Really.

659
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:46,150
Hello?

660
00:40:46,150 --> 00:40:47,950
Hey, Jae Pil.

661
00:40:49,620 --> 00:40:51,810
You were home.

662
00:40:51,810 --> 00:40:54,480
I wondered if I should call later.

663
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:56,660
I just got home.

664
00:40:56,660 --> 00:40:58,490
What made you call at this hour?

665
00:40:58,490 --> 00:41:00,080
Shouldn't you be busy right now?

666
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:02,780
I was. I was really busy.

667
00:41:02,780 --> 00:41:04,560
There was an accident at a construction site.

668
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:07,750
I'm finally catching a breath now.

669
00:41:07,750 --> 00:41:10,310
You must be exhausted.

670
00:41:10,310 --> 00:41:11,740
Well,

671
00:41:12,530 --> 00:41:15,190
are you free this Sunday?

672
00:41:15,190 --> 00:41:19,530
Yes. The hair salon is closed
on the second Sunday. Why?

673
00:41:19,530 --> 00:41:21,400
It's nothing much.

674
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:25,830
There's this Medical Students' Night.
It's an annual event.

675
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:31,420
They charge a fine if I don't bring a date.

676
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:38,290
I was wondering if you could come with me.

677
00:41:38,290 --> 00:41:40,210
A date?

678
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:50,980
Well, I don't mind.

679
00:41:50,980 --> 00:41:54,040
But are you sure I can come?

680
00:41:57,730 --> 00:42:00,110
Okay. I'll go, then.

681
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:02,900
Yes, yes. I know that hotel.

682
00:42:02,900 --> 00:42:06,070
Okay. I'll see you at the entrance.

683
00:42:06,070 --> 00:42:08,470
Okay, okay. Bye.

684
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:10,810
Date? What date?

685
00:42:10,810 --> 00:42:13,330
- Jae Pil asked you to be your date?
- Date?

686
00:42:13,330 --> 00:42:14,780
Come on and tell us.

687
00:42:14,780 --> 00:42:17,670
Come on! I'm dying to know.

688
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:21,140
There's an event called the Medical
Students' Night or whatever.

689
00:42:21,140 --> 00:42:23,830
He asked me to come since there'll be
a fine if he doesn't bring a date.

690
00:42:23,830 --> 00:42:26,190
- Unni!
- It's happening. It's happening.

691
00:42:26,190 --> 00:42:28,810
You think he called you because of a fine?

692
00:42:28,810 --> 00:42:30,490
He's definitely confessing his love.

693
00:42:30,490 --> 00:42:33,340
He finally made up his mind.

694
00:42:33,340 --> 00:42:34,700
It's a love confession. It has to be.

695
00:42:34,700 --> 00:42:37,250
Unni, Unni. Stay alert and listen.

696
00:42:37,250 --> 00:42:39,130
This is your moment.

697
00:42:39,130 --> 00:42:42,060
You can't mess this up.
You know what I mean, right?

698
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:44,870
My moment, my foot. Stop freaking out.

699
00:42:44,870 --> 00:42:47,340
Hey, Ko Yeong Rye. Ko Yeong Rye.

700
00:42:47,340 --> 00:42:50,450
How could we not freak out right now?

701
00:42:50,450 --> 00:42:52,840
Do something. Seriously.

702
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:54,900
You'll be a fool to miss this chance.

703
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:57,770
- Come on-
- Stop, stop. Stop.

704
00:42:57,770 --> 00:43:00,070
That's enough.

705
00:43:00,070 --> 00:43:05,100
Well, I... We just think you make a nice couple.

706
00:43:05,100 --> 00:43:07,370
Yes. We thought it was such a shame.

707
00:43:07,370 --> 00:43:10,300
I know. I do, but...

708
00:43:10,300 --> 00:43:14,560
I can manage my dating life. So, be quiet.

709
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:32,010
Of course it is.

710
00:43:32,950 --> 00:43:35,240
I'm asking because it's you.

711
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:38,060
"Because it's you..."

712
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:43,560
"Because it's you..."

713
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:55,290
What does that mean?

714
00:43:55,290 --> 00:43:58,640
Because he feels comfortable with me?

715
00:43:58,640 --> 00:44:00,550
Because we're close?

716
00:44:01,540 --> 00:44:05,380
If not, because...

717
00:44:05,380 --> 00:44:07,480
Because he likes me?

718
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:19,840
Ma'am, hold on! Hold on.

719
00:44:19,840 --> 00:44:21,630
Hold on.

720
00:44:22,310 --> 00:44:25,590
The roses... Give me a box of roses.

721
00:44:25,590 --> 00:44:28,610
The gift box. The orange ones.

722
00:44:28,610 --> 00:44:31,130
[Orange roses - Shy first love]

723
00:44:31,130 --> 00:44:35,470
[Gimpo International Airport]

724
00:44:59,790 --> 00:45:03,590
Hi, Mr. Jeong. Have you been well?

725
00:45:08,540 --> 00:45:09,960
I just got into the car, Mother.

726
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:12,540
I see. You must be tired.

727
00:45:12,540 --> 00:45:15,060
Be careful and take your time. Hurry up.

728
00:45:15,060 --> 00:45:17,950
Is it because I haven't heard Korean in a while?

729
00:45:17,950 --> 00:45:22,320
I don't know how to be careful,
take my time, and hurry up.

730
00:45:23,270 --> 00:45:25,730
I'll stop by somewhere first, Mother.

731
00:45:25,730 --> 00:45:28,150
I know you miss me, but please wait a bit.

732
00:45:28,150 --> 00:45:29,210
[Court]

733
00:45:29,210 --> 00:45:30,800
Witness Jang Yeon Hui, who will prove
[Judge]

734
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:33,860
the defendant's alibi doesn't
remember being with the

735
00:45:33,860 --> 00:45:36,730
defendant at the time of the crime.

736
00:45:36,730 --> 00:45:41,830
It's hard to accept the defendant's
statement based on what the witness said.

737
00:45:41,830 --> 00:45:44,680
On the other hand, the statement from
Kim Yeong Su, the victim and the witness

738
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:49,170
has been consistent since he talked to the police.

739
00:45:49,170 --> 00:45:51,330
For these reasons,

740
00:45:51,330 --> 00:45:53,760
Kim Yeong Su's statement is highly credible

741
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:58,360
and it's very unlikely that the
defendant isn't the culprit.

742
00:45:58,360 --> 00:46:00,490
The defendant's indictment

743
00:46:00,490 --> 00:46:03,860
was determined by solid evidence

744
00:46:03,860 --> 00:46:08,450
that leaves me with no reasonable doubt.

745
00:46:08,450 --> 00:46:11,690
Therefore, I reached the following ruling.

746
00:46:11,690 --> 00:46:16,360
The defendant will face a fine of two million won.

747
00:46:23,050 --> 00:46:25,830
Trainee Ko Yeong Sik,

748
00:46:25,830 --> 00:46:31,240
could you tell us more about
why you found the defendant guilty?

749
00:46:31,240 --> 00:46:35,420
According to the Principle of Adjudication
Based on Evidence in Criminal Law,

750
00:46:35,420 --> 00:46:39,800
a crime must be proven beyond a reasonable doubt.

751
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:45,990
In this case, the defense's witness
couldn't prove the defendant's alibi

752
00:46:45,990 --> 00:46:50,630
and the prosecution's witness,
the victim's statement was highly credible.

753
00:46:50,630 --> 00:46:53,380
I decided based on that.

754
00:46:53,380 --> 00:46:56,130
Good. All right.

755
00:46:56,130 --> 00:46:59,410
A witness's statement isn't solid evidence,

756
00:46:59,410 --> 00:47:04,060
but if the judge was left with no reasonable doubt

757
00:47:04,060 --> 00:47:06,930
since the statement seemed highly credible,

758
00:47:06,930 --> 00:47:10,610
it can become important evidence for a ruling.

759
00:47:11,610 --> 00:47:14,510
Good work, Trainee Ko Yeong Sik.

760
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:19,770
You were so passionate today.

761
00:47:19,770 --> 00:47:21,090
You must be hungry.

762
00:47:21,090 --> 00:47:22,580
Let's go. I'll buy you a meal.

763
00:47:22,580 --> 00:47:24,570
No, I have to finish up. Eat without me.

764
00:47:24,570 --> 00:47:25,820
Please, let's eat.

765
00:47:25,820 --> 00:47:28,600
I'm not asking you to pay. I'm paying.

766
00:47:28,600 --> 00:47:30,380
You're hurting my feelings.

767
00:47:30,380 --> 00:47:32,060
Ko Yeong Sik.

768
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,720
Our future judge.

769
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:36,170
What are you doing here?

770
00:47:36,170 --> 00:47:37,860
I'm here, obviously.

771
00:47:37,860 --> 00:47:39,290
Come here.

772
00:47:41,770 --> 00:47:43,680
- Hey-
- Keep your distance.

773
00:47:43,680 --> 00:47:45,180
Geez. Come on.

774
00:47:45,180 --> 00:47:46,850
Hello.

775
00:47:51,270 --> 00:47:52,560
When did you come back?

776
00:47:52,560 --> 00:47:54,140
You didn't mention this in your letter.

777
00:47:54,140 --> 00:47:55,660
Today.

778
00:47:55,660 --> 00:47:59,690
It won't be a surprise if I tell you in advance.

779
00:47:59,690 --> 00:48:02,550
Do I get arrested if I swear at a future judge?

780
00:48:02,550 --> 00:48:04,530
Gosh, I'm scared.

781
00:48:04,530 --> 00:48:06,800
You're still just as silly.

782
00:48:06,800 --> 00:48:10,120
- Are you back for good?
- Yeah.

783
00:48:10,120 --> 00:48:12,720
I couldn't stay longer.
My father's getting old, too.

784
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:14,800
I think I should take over the company.

785
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:18,400
Yes. It was going to happen, anyway.
Good thinking.

786
00:48:20,620 --> 00:48:23,710
Why don't you date, by the way?

787
00:48:23,710 --> 00:48:29,080
I could tell that the smart young lady
seemed a bit interested in you.

788
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:31,570
Do you like someone already?

789
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:35,440
Huh?

790
00:48:35,440 --> 00:48:37,420
No, I don't.

791
00:48:37,420 --> 00:48:41,100
Making money for siblings' education
and helping Mother is already a handful.

792
00:48:41,100 --> 00:48:44,540
Oh, your mother. She's well, right?

793
00:48:45,540 --> 00:48:49,360
I missed her soybean paste stew
so much while in the US.

794
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:51,370
Yeong Bae and Yeong Mi must be all grown, too.

795
00:48:51,370 --> 00:48:54,840
Right. Yeong Rye. Is she doing well?

796
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:18,900
[The 10th Glorious Yeonseo Medical Students' Night]

797
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:25,510
Thank you.

798
00:49:31,550 --> 00:49:33,130
Hi.

799
00:49:46,020 --> 00:49:48,030
I'm here.

800
00:49:56,420 --> 00:49:59,120
Who are you? Do you know me?

801
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:01,220
Hey, don't do that.

802
00:50:01,220 --> 00:50:06,820
I want to hide because I feel
embarrassed and awkward.

803
00:50:06,820 --> 00:50:09,540
- So, who-
- Seriously.

804
00:50:09,540 --> 00:50:11,030
Okay.

805
00:50:11,030 --> 00:50:14,640
I was surprised because you look so different.

806
00:50:14,640 --> 00:50:15,910
Do I look that weird?

807
00:50:15,910 --> 00:50:17,810
Is my makeup too much? Should I remove it?

808
00:50:17,810 --> 00:50:19,310
No. It's nice.

809
00:50:19,310 --> 00:50:21,540
No, no. I should remove it. It's no good.

810
00:50:21,540 --> 00:50:23,620
I said it's okay.

811
00:50:26,880 --> 00:50:29,300
You look pretty. I mean it.

812
00:50:29,300 --> 00:50:32,010
Geez. You don't mean it.

813
00:50:35,820 --> 00:50:38,570
Shall we go inside, my date?

814
00:50:38,570 --> 00:50:40,890
Forget it.

815
00:50:40,890 --> 00:50:42,410
Let's go.

816
00:50:45,950 --> 00:50:51,040
[The 10th Glorious Yeonseo Medical Students' Night]

817
00:50:53,030 --> 00:50:54,320
What?

818
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:56,550
Is something bothering you?

819
00:50:56,550 --> 00:50:59,070
No. Is it because I'm nervous?

820
00:50:59,070 --> 00:51:01,660
I feel a bit nauseated.

821
00:51:01,660 --> 00:51:04,200
That's no good. Should I get you some medicine?

822
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:06,610
No. It's not that bad.

823
00:51:06,610 --> 00:51:09,250
I'll be okay soon.

824
00:51:09,250 --> 00:51:10,670
Let's go.

825
00:51:10,670 --> 00:51:12,150
This way.

826
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:31,030
- J-Jong Hui?
- Yeong Rye!

827
00:51:37,820 --> 00:51:40,450
Excuse me. Excuse me.

828
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:44,130
Who are you?

829
00:51:45,860 --> 00:51:50,100
I'm sorry. I thought you were someone else.

830
00:51:56,190 --> 00:51:57,940
What is it, Yeong Rye?

831
00:51:57,940 --> 00:51:59,710
What's going on?

832
00:52:02,790 --> 00:52:04,320
Are you okay?

833
00:52:10,010 --> 00:52:12,400
[The 10th Glorious Yeonseo Medical Students' Night]

834
00:52:19,290 --> 00:52:21,010
Let me see.

835
00:52:21,010 --> 00:52:23,540
Let's do a cold compress before it gets swollen.

836
00:52:23,540 --> 00:52:25,230
Is it ice?

837
00:52:25,230 --> 00:52:26,540
Where did you get this?

838
00:52:26,540 --> 00:52:28,250
It was an emergency.

839
00:52:28,250 --> 00:52:30,130
I broke the ice sculpture.

840
00:52:30,130 --> 00:52:32,180
What? Hey.

841
00:52:32,180 --> 00:52:34,430
I'm joking.

842
00:52:34,430 --> 00:52:37,810
I got some from the hotel restaurant.

843
00:52:37,810 --> 00:52:40,500
Seriously.

844
00:52:43,990 --> 00:52:45,520
Cold.

845
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:49,950
It's cold.

846
00:52:52,490 --> 00:52:55,350
Looks like it's already swollen.

847
00:52:57,500 --> 00:52:59,930
It'll be hard to walk.

848
00:52:59,930 --> 00:53:03,350
What did you see? What made you run like that?

849
00:53:03,350 --> 00:53:06,160
Did you see a celebrity or something?

850
00:53:09,990 --> 00:53:12,960
Come to the hospital if it's still
swollen tomorrow morning.

851
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:14,790
We'll take an X-ray.

852
00:53:14,790 --> 00:53:16,160
Okay.

853
00:53:19,810 --> 00:53:21,590
This is no good.

854
00:53:21,590 --> 00:53:23,150
Let's go home. I'll drive you.

855
00:53:23,150 --> 00:53:25,850
Hey. No, no. You should go back in.

856
00:53:25,850 --> 00:53:28,250
I can take a taxi. I can go on my own.

857
00:53:28,250 --> 00:53:30,790
It's okay. It'd bother me if I didn't.

858
00:53:30,790 --> 00:53:33,600
I was regretting attending
an event like this, anyway.

859
00:53:33,600 --> 00:53:36,640
I'll just be hated by the seniors and pay the fine.

860
00:53:43,630 --> 00:53:45,270
Give me your hand.

861
00:53:55,710 --> 00:53:58,940
Gosh. Eat slowly. You'll get indigestion.

862
00:53:58,940 --> 00:54:00,940
I'll give you more rice, okay?

863
00:54:00,940 --> 00:54:03,710
There's a lot. There's plenty back there.

864
00:54:03,710 --> 00:54:07,420
Okay, Mother. I missed this so much.
You see the tear here, right?

865
00:54:07,420 --> 00:54:08,870
Gosh. No.

866
00:54:08,870 --> 00:54:12,380
Do you want to start a restaurant
in Koreatown? I'll invest.

867
00:54:12,380 --> 00:54:13,980
You'll be the owner, and I'll be the advisor.

868
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:17,150
I'm sure it will easily be a hit.

869
00:54:17,150 --> 00:54:19,610
You got better at flattering.

870
00:54:19,610 --> 00:54:21,280
Is it because you've been eating butter?

871
00:54:21,280 --> 00:54:25,830
Whoa. You used to ask if I put sesame oil
on my tongue. You're so creative.

872
00:54:25,830 --> 00:54:28,540
Okay. That's enough. Finish your food.

873
00:54:28,540 --> 00:54:30,810
- Aren't you going to go home?
- Right.

874
00:54:30,810 --> 00:54:33,860
I've always preferred your home over mine.

875
00:54:33,860 --> 00:54:36,320
- Why is that?
- It's because of the food, obviously.

876
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,370
You're right. It's the food.

877
00:54:38,370 --> 00:54:41,110
I love Mother's cooking so much.

878
00:54:42,470 --> 00:54:45,120
Eat a lot.

879
00:54:45,120 --> 00:54:48,150
It should be nutty and tasty.

880
00:54:48,150 --> 00:54:50,270
You, too, Judge Ko.

881
00:54:50,270 --> 00:54:53,200
I'm not a judge. I'm still a trainee.

882
00:54:53,200 --> 00:54:55,340
Who cares about that?

883
00:54:55,340 --> 00:54:59,380
You'll become a judge soon. What's the difference?

884
00:54:59,380 --> 00:55:02,110
Yes. You're so impressive, Mother.

885
00:55:02,110 --> 00:55:06,960
Everyone knows he passed the
national exam, thanks to you.

886
00:55:06,960 --> 00:55:08,020
You know, too, right?

887
00:55:08,020 --> 00:55:09,690
If you don't, you're not even human.

888
00:55:09,690 --> 00:55:12,040
I know. So, calm down and eat.

889
00:55:12,040 --> 00:55:13,370
Okay.

890
00:55:14,860 --> 00:55:16,670
When is Yeong Rye coming home?

891
00:55:16,670 --> 00:55:18,310
Is she getting off work late?

892
00:55:18,310 --> 00:55:19,880
She had no work today.

893
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:21,860
She went on a date.

894
00:55:26,820 --> 00:55:28,580
A date?

895
00:55:28,580 --> 00:55:30,300
What date?

896
00:55:30,300 --> 00:55:31,410
[Yeongeun Market]

897
00:55:44,780 --> 00:55:46,550
Hey, it's okay.

898
00:55:46,550 --> 00:55:48,370
I can go inside now.

899
00:55:48,370 --> 00:55:50,200
You should get going now.

900
00:55:50,200 --> 00:55:52,740
I wouldn't have gotten off if I were to do that.

901
00:55:56,480 --> 00:55:57,840
Here.

902
00:55:57,840 --> 00:55:59,250
What?

903
00:56:04,450 --> 00:56:05,990
Here.

904
00:56:05,990 --> 00:56:07,670
What?

905
00:56:07,670 --> 00:56:10,360
Your foot will swell again
if you walk on it. Come on.

906
00:56:10,360 --> 00:56:13,680
Hey, it's okay. It's not that bad.

907
00:56:13,680 --> 00:56:15,920
And I'm heavy.

908
00:56:15,920 --> 00:56:19,400
How heavy could you be? Don't resist. Come on.

909
00:56:20,400 --> 00:56:22,350
You can't overuse it.

910
00:56:22,350 --> 00:56:24,180
I'm a doctor.

911
00:56:28,710 --> 00:56:30,840
Aigoo, my legs.

912
00:56:30,840 --> 00:56:33,320
Hurry unless you want to punish me.

913
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:38,610
You... You'd better not regret this.
I'll get on your back.

914
00:56:38,610 --> 00:56:40,760
Okay? I warned you.

915
00:56:41,600 --> 00:56:43,320
I'm so scared.

916
00:56:44,410 --> 00:56:45,480
Here I go.

917
00:56:45,480 --> 00:56:47,510
Okay. I'm ready.

918
00:56:47,510 --> 00:56:55,180
♫ When darkness falls in my quiet heart ♫

919
00:56:55,180 --> 00:57:01,810
♫ Outside is filled with so many stars ♫

920
00:57:03,060 --> 00:57:04,760
Aigoo...

921
00:57:06,050 --> 00:57:09,250
Are you a feather or a human?

922
00:57:10,660 --> 00:57:13,390
You should eat more.

923
00:57:13,390 --> 00:57:16,230
How are you on your feet all day?

924
00:57:17,130 --> 00:57:21,700
You say that, but you seem to be struggling.

925
00:57:21,700 --> 00:57:25,500
Me? No. I'm not struggling at all.

926
00:57:26,500 --> 00:57:29,690
Hey, you'll fall.

927
00:57:29,690 --> 00:57:31,250
Don't do it.

928
00:57:31,250 --> 00:57:32,980
Did you see that?

929
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:42,390
- Hey.
- Gosh, ma'am. Spare me.

930
00:57:43,870 --> 00:57:45,350
Are you okay?

931
00:57:48,650 --> 00:57:50,350
Thank you, Han Jae Pil.

932
00:57:50,350 --> 00:57:53,630
I got home comfortably, thanks to you.
But what about you?

933
00:57:53,630 --> 00:57:56,240
Will your seniors really hate you now?

934
00:57:56,240 --> 00:57:59,420
Gosh, whatever. Let them.

935
00:58:00,350 --> 00:58:03,500
I was a rebel. Don't you remember?

936
00:58:03,500 --> 00:58:05,190
Of course, I do.

937
00:58:05,190 --> 00:58:09,490
You went on a blind date in 12th grade.
That tells you everything.

938
00:58:09,490 --> 00:58:11,760
I know. Go inside now.

939
00:58:11,760 --> 00:58:15,380
Do another cold compress before bed.

940
00:58:19,340 --> 00:58:21,180
Well...

941
00:58:29,200 --> 00:58:31,170
Hey, Yeong Rye.

942
00:58:32,340 --> 00:58:33,450
Jeong Hyeon?

943
00:58:33,450 --> 00:58:36,210
Wow. How did you get so pretty, Ugly?

944
00:58:36,210 --> 00:58:37,980
You're making me worry.

945
00:58:37,980 --> 00:58:41,930
I'd feel more comfortable if you stayed ugly.

946
00:58:41,930 --> 00:58:44,170
Oppa, when did you come to Korea?

947
00:58:44,170 --> 00:58:46,120
I didn't hear that you were back.

948
00:58:46,120 --> 00:58:50,190
Today. I wanted to have Mother's
soybean paste stew first.

949
00:58:51,930 --> 00:58:55,690
Wow, Jae Pil. Long time no see.

950
00:58:55,690 --> 00:58:59,750
Wow. You're starting to look like a doctor.

951
00:58:59,750 --> 00:59:02,130
Have you been well?

952
00:59:02,130 --> 00:59:04,830
It's so nice to run into you.

953
00:59:20,060 --> 00:59:22,770
- Another bottle, please.
- Okay.

954
00:59:23,710 --> 00:59:26,790
Yeong Rye's friend told me earlier.

955
00:59:26,790 --> 00:59:28,910
I heard you guys went to the
Medical Students' Night.

956
00:59:28,910 --> 00:59:31,800
I guess you don't have a girlfriend
since you brought Yeong Rye.

957
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:33,510
Well, no.

958
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:38,870
But you should've taken good care of her.

959
00:59:38,870 --> 00:59:41,700
Why did you let her sprain her ankle?

960
00:59:41,700 --> 00:59:43,270
How's that Jae Pil's fault?

961
00:59:43,270 --> 00:59:45,800
It's because she was clumsy.

962
00:59:45,800 --> 00:59:49,670
I suppose. That's her charm, right?

963
00:59:51,410 --> 00:59:54,260
Unpolished, you know?

964
00:59:59,870 --> 01:00:02,790
I missed Yeong Rye. That was too brief.

965
01:00:02,790 --> 01:00:05,010
Should I bring her back here?

966
01:00:05,010 --> 01:00:07,200
I can carry her myself.

967
01:00:07,200 --> 01:00:09,350
She can't drink right now.

968
01:00:09,350 --> 01:00:11,820
Because of the inflammation.

969
01:00:11,820 --> 01:00:13,710
Really?

970
01:00:13,710 --> 01:00:18,350
I have nothing to say since
it's coming from a doctor.

971
01:00:35,300 --> 01:00:36,550
Thank you.

972
01:00:36,550 --> 01:00:38,250
Enjoy.

973
01:00:41,100 --> 01:00:43,800
- Another bottle, please.
- Okay.

974
01:01:07,400 --> 01:01:09,610
Just give us two bottles.

975
01:01:09,610 --> 01:01:11,050
Okay.

976
01:01:36,030 --> 01:01:39,670
Geez, man. So...

977
01:01:39,670 --> 01:01:42,730
you shouldn't have even tried.

978
01:02:31,380 --> 01:02:32,910
Excuse me.

979
01:03:05,380 --> 01:03:07,690
This is "Awake in the Night."

980
01:03:07,690 --> 01:03:10,750
We got a letter from one of our regulars.

981
01:03:10,750 --> 01:03:14,020
Our listeners cheer for this person, too.

982
01:03:14,020 --> 01:03:15,600
It's Ms. K from Dodam-dong.

983
01:03:15,600 --> 01:03:18,400
Let's hear her story.

984
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:21,120
I heard there's such a thing as a Rose Day

985
01:03:21,120 --> 01:03:24,220
for the first time today.

986
01:03:24,220 --> 01:03:29,340
You're supposed to confess your love
to someone by giving them roses.

987
01:03:29,340 --> 01:03:31,890
I couldn't muster the courage on Valentine's Day,

988
01:03:31,890 --> 01:03:34,240
but I'll try this time.

989
01:03:34,240 --> 01:03:38,250
I'm worried things might get awkward between us,

990
01:03:38,250 --> 01:03:40,680
but I'll no longer ignore my feelings

991
01:03:40,680 --> 01:03:44,200
that I've had for a long time.

992
01:03:44,200 --> 01:03:49,510
She requested Yu Jae Ha's "Love On My Heart."

993
01:03:49,510 --> 01:03:52,230
I'm so curious about how it'd go.

994
01:03:52,230 --> 01:03:54,610
If her love confession worked out,

995
01:03:54,610 --> 01:03:57,670
she might not be listening to this right now.

996
01:03:57,670 --> 01:03:59,710
I hope that's the case.

997
01:03:59,710 --> 01:04:01,810
Let's listen to the song now.

998
01:04:01,810 --> 01:04:05,412
Yu Jae Ha's "Love On My Heart."

999
01:04:05,412 --> 01:04:12,552
♫ The pieces of the dream that
can't be put back together ♫

1000
01:04:13,590 --> 01:04:17,220
♫ They're going missing one by one ♫

1001
01:04:17,220 --> 01:04:24,400
My love confession failed since
I missed the right timing-

1002
01:04:24,400 --> 01:04:28,550
♫ Wandering endlessly ♫

1003
01:04:29,580 --> 01:04:36,300
♫ I'm hanging in there today, too ♫

1004
01:04:36,300 --> 01:04:37,620
What?

1005
01:04:37,620 --> 01:04:39,960
What's wrong with them? What happened?

1006
01:04:39,960 --> 01:04:41,730
I don't know.

1007
01:04:41,730 --> 01:04:45,560
I almost died carrying these two drunken men.

1008
01:04:45,560 --> 01:04:47,670
Gosh, these bastards.

1009
01:04:47,670 --> 01:04:50,350
What? Where am I?

1010
01:04:50,350 --> 01:04:52,730
It's too dark.

1011
01:04:53,940 --> 01:04:56,120
How funny.

1012
01:04:56,120 --> 01:04:59,200
You don't know someone until they're drunk.

1013
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:03,150
Now that they're drunk, the one
who studied abroad or the doctor

1014
01:05:03,150 --> 01:05:04,830
aren't so different. Don't you agree?

1015
01:05:04,830 --> 01:05:06,440
I know.

1016
01:05:06,440 --> 01:05:09,100
I really thought he was cool.

1017
01:05:09,100 --> 01:05:12,010
But this is a bit disappointing.

1018
01:05:12,010 --> 01:05:13,830
Geez.

1019
01:05:18,090 --> 01:05:20,300
Huh? Gosh.

1020
01:05:27,670 --> 01:05:30,340
Hey, move.

1021
01:05:33,520 --> 01:05:35,710
My arm hurts.

1022
01:05:36,770 --> 01:05:40,410
Hey, hey. I have a cramp. Don't move.

1023
01:05:43,610 --> 01:05:45,470
Who are these men?

1024
01:05:45,470 --> 01:05:47,770
Why are they sleeping in our house?

1025
01:05:47,770 --> 01:05:51,240
Gosh, I know. Why here?

1026
01:05:51,240 --> 01:05:53,300
Hi, guys.

1027
01:05:54,080 --> 01:05:57,460
Mom wants you to come down and eat.

1028
01:05:57,460 --> 01:05:59,590
Both of you.

1029
01:05:59,590 --> 01:06:01,760
Hey, cure your hangover.

1030
01:06:20,720 --> 01:06:22,470
We're here.

1031
01:06:23,310 --> 01:06:25,290
You came.

1032
01:06:27,680 --> 01:06:29,750
What are you doing? Have a seat.

1033
01:06:29,750 --> 01:06:33,970
Okay. Dried pollack soup? You're the best, Mother.

1034
01:06:36,170 --> 01:06:37,970
Thank you.

1035
01:06:38,890 --> 01:06:40,470
What happened to you?

1036
01:06:40,470 --> 01:06:42,540
Don't know. I'm dying.

1037
01:06:51,350 --> 01:06:52,810
Okay. Let's eat.

1038
01:06:52,810 --> 01:06:55,100
Thank you for the meal!

1039
01:06:55,100 --> 01:06:56,900
Whoa...

1040
01:07:01,240 --> 01:07:05,060
You've been consumed by alcohol. Totally.

1041
01:07:05,990 --> 01:07:09,220
It's painful and embarrassing, isn't it?

1042
01:07:09,220 --> 01:07:11,740
And you have nothing to say with your big mouth.

1043
01:07:11,740 --> 01:07:13,680
I know.

1044
01:07:13,680 --> 01:07:18,430
I haven't had soju in a while. It tasted so sweet.

1045
01:07:18,430 --> 01:07:19,940
I'm sorry.

1046
01:07:19,940 --> 01:07:23,480
Gosh. It's fine. Just eat and go.

1047
01:07:23,480 --> 01:07:25,970
Jae Pil, don't you have
to go back to the hospital?

1048
01:07:25,970 --> 01:07:28,330
Well, yes. I have some time today.

1049
01:07:28,330 --> 01:07:30,870
We can go in late today because
of the event last night.

1050
01:07:30,870 --> 01:07:36,340
So, you want to eat lunch and dinner here, too?

1051
01:07:36,340 --> 01:07:38,130
No, no. It's not that.

1052
01:07:38,130 --> 01:07:40,480
Gosh. What's with this jangjorim*?
(Beef braised in soy sauce)

1053
01:07:40,480 --> 01:07:43,140
It's so delicious. Wow.

1054
01:07:43,140 --> 01:07:47,120
Yeong Rye, eat this. It's a big piece.

1055
01:07:50,460 --> 01:07:53,410
Jae Pil! Jae Pil!

1056
01:07:53,410 --> 01:07:56,870
I heard... I heard you got drunk
and passed out here.

1057
01:07:59,010 --> 01:08:00,940
Hello, Mother.

1058
01:08:01,960 --> 01:08:04,170
That silly guy.

1059
01:08:12,370 --> 01:08:15,340
Wow. You're unbelievable, Han Jae Pil.

1060
01:08:15,340 --> 01:08:18,840
You don't even drink much. Why...

1061
01:08:18,840 --> 01:08:22,900
Was it Jeong Hyeon? I heard you had
a drinking competition with him.

1062
01:08:22,900 --> 01:08:27,360
Why did you suddenly get
competitive? It's unlike you.

1063
01:08:27,360 --> 01:08:30,230
Let's drive quietly. You're annoying me.

1064
01:08:30,230 --> 01:08:34,340
I don't want to. I'll make fun of you
for the rest of your life.

1065
01:08:35,340 --> 01:08:36,340
I'll get off.

1066
01:08:36,340 --> 01:08:38,280
Hey, hey. Okay, okay, okay.

1067
01:08:38,280 --> 01:08:40,070
Okay, okay, okay.

1068
01:08:40,070 --> 01:08:42,180
Okay, okay.

1069
01:08:44,140 --> 01:08:46,260
You said you'll stop by home, right?

1070
01:08:46,260 --> 01:08:48,840
- I'll drop you off on the main street.
- Okay.

1071
01:08:52,770 --> 01:08:56,160
I heard there was an event at your school.

1072
01:08:56,160 --> 01:09:02,110
Ho Suk freaked out about you
inviting Yeong Rye there.

1073
01:09:02,110 --> 01:09:04,080
What? About what?

1074
01:09:04,080 --> 01:09:06,480
What do you think?

1075
01:09:06,480 --> 01:09:11,750
You're neither friends nor
a couple with Yeong Rye.

1076
01:09:11,750 --> 01:09:14,070
It's such an awkward relationship.

1077
01:09:14,070 --> 01:09:17,200
That's why everyone's freaking out.

1078
01:09:17,200 --> 01:09:20,590
Let's hear how you actually feel.

1079
01:09:20,590 --> 01:09:24,850
What is Yeong Rye to you?

1080
01:09:25,900 --> 01:09:29,000
Hey, hold on. I have the right to ask this.

1081
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:30,720
You know she was my first love, right?

1082
01:09:30,720 --> 01:09:33,230
How could I not know? You let everyone know.

1083
01:09:33,230 --> 01:09:35,110
That's what I'm saying.

1084
01:09:35,110 --> 01:09:36,940
How do you really feel?

1085
01:09:36,940 --> 01:09:40,650
She's just a friend to you?

1086
01:09:47,680 --> 01:09:49,540
No.

1087
01:09:49,540 --> 01:09:51,630
No? Right.

1088
01:09:52,630 --> 01:09:56,380
No? H-Hey, did you say, "No" just now?

1089
01:09:56,380 --> 01:09:58,270
How do you feel about her, then-

1090
01:09:58,270 --> 01:10:01,580
Hey, don't let go of this!

1091
01:10:01,580 --> 01:10:03,590
- This is a steering wheel.
- Okay.

1092
01:10:03,590 --> 01:10:05,270
Geez. Are you crazy?

1093
01:10:05,270 --> 01:10:08,380
Okay, okay, okay.

1094
01:10:12,320 --> 01:10:14,780
So, what is Yeong Rye to you?

1095
01:10:14,780 --> 01:10:17,840
Is she more than a friend?

1096
01:10:17,840 --> 01:10:21,250
I asked what she means to you!

1097
01:10:22,240 --> 01:10:24,700
Hello.

1098
01:10:24,700 --> 01:10:26,740
Hello.

1099
01:10:27,650 --> 01:10:30,040
Is something going on? What's happening?

1100
01:10:30,040 --> 01:10:33,160
We're expecting a VVIP customer today.

1101
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:35,870
But she's bringing her daughter, too.

1102
01:10:35,870 --> 01:10:37,550
The owner is extra irritable today.

1103
01:10:37,550 --> 01:10:41,460
Hey, don't put the planter
in the front. Put it over there.

1104
01:10:41,460 --> 01:10:42,740
Hello.

1105
01:10:42,740 --> 01:10:45,330
Yeong Rye, what are you doing?
Get changed and help.

1106
01:10:45,330 --> 01:10:47,050
- Okay.
- Where's Choi Jeong Bun?

1107
01:10:47,050 --> 01:10:48,420
She's off today.

1108
01:10:48,420 --> 01:10:50,070
Go.

1109
01:10:50,070 --> 01:10:53,050
Hey, put the mop inside!

1110
01:10:54,250 --> 01:10:56,980
Nothing's better than sweet coffee in the morning.

1111
01:10:56,980 --> 01:10:59,040
Of course.

1112
01:10:59,040 --> 01:11:01,000
The owner is overreacting.

1113
01:11:01,000 --> 01:11:03,950
So what if a VVIP is coming?
Does she have to freak out?

1114
01:11:03,950 --> 01:11:06,180
You know how greedy she is.

1115
01:11:06,180 --> 01:11:07,900
Don't you know?

1116
01:11:07,900 --> 01:11:10,590
She was a protege of Michelle,
the best in the field.

1117
01:11:10,590 --> 01:11:13,200
But she betrayed her and opened this place.

1118
01:11:13,200 --> 01:11:15,280
She stole all of her regulars, too.

1119
01:11:15,280 --> 01:11:17,230
I heard about that.

1120
01:11:17,230 --> 01:11:20,960
Who's the VVIP who's coming today, anyway?

1121
01:11:20,960 --> 01:11:22,330
I don't know the details.

1122
01:11:22,330 --> 01:11:26,510
Daeyang Group's chairwoman?
And her only daughter, apparently.

1123
01:11:27,610 --> 01:11:29,640
So envious.

1124
01:11:29,640 --> 01:11:31,270
Ready, go.

1125
01:11:31,270 --> 01:11:33,830
Welcome to Jullee Beauty Salon.

1126
01:11:33,830 --> 01:11:36,290
Bend your backs more. Go again.

1127
01:11:36,290 --> 01:11:39,170
Welcome to Jullee Beauty Salon.

1128
01:11:39,170 --> 01:11:43,250
You're wondering why I'm making
a fuss first thing in the morning.

1129
01:11:43,250 --> 01:11:44,820
How should I say?

1130
01:11:44,820 --> 01:11:49,040
There's a clear difference
between a VIP and a VVIP.

1131
01:11:49,040 --> 01:11:50,300
What's the difference?

1132
01:11:50,300 --> 01:11:51,480
Clear difference.

1133
01:11:51,480 --> 01:11:54,210
It's their influence.

1134
01:11:54,210 --> 01:11:56,930
Rather than having 10 VIPs,

1135
01:11:56,930 --> 01:12:04,810
I'm saying having one VVIP here
has a bigger impact.

1136
01:12:04,810 --> 01:12:07,430
So, what are we supposed to do today?

1137
01:12:07,430 --> 01:12:09,390
We need to do a good job.

1138
01:12:10,170 --> 01:12:13,560
You need to hold onto that VVIP.
That's what I'm saying.

1139
01:12:13,560 --> 01:12:14,670
Do you understand?

1140
01:12:14,670 --> 01:12:16,330
Yes.

1141
01:12:18,480 --> 01:12:20,730
I'll be in charge of the chairwoman myself.

1142
01:12:20,730 --> 01:12:23,260
- Manager Jo.
- Yes.

1143
01:12:23,260 --> 01:12:26,030
Be in charge of her daughter.

1144
01:12:26,030 --> 01:12:28,650
You know the younger ones are more picky, right?

1145
01:12:28,650 --> 01:12:32,470
Dry and comb thoroughly and smoothly. Okay?

1146
01:12:32,470 --> 01:12:34,170
Okay. Got it.

1147
01:12:34,170 --> 01:12:35,200
They're here.

1148
01:12:35,200 --> 01:12:37,750
Okay. Let's get ready.

1149
01:12:52,680 --> 01:12:57,030
Gosh. Chairwoman, you came.

1150
01:12:57,030 --> 01:12:59,470
Welcome.

1151
01:12:59,470 --> 01:13:01,060
Come this way.

1152
01:13:01,970 --> 01:13:04,340
Chairwoman, please watch the steps.

1153
01:13:06,050 --> 01:13:10,010
Welcome to Jullee Beauty Salon.

1154
01:14:19,370 --> 01:14:23,630
Hello. I'm a staff designer, Ko Yeong Rye.

1155
01:14:23,630 --> 01:14:25,640
I'm in your care.

1156
01:14:26,420 --> 01:14:28,060
- Oh, my gosh!
- Can't you be careful?

1157
01:14:28,060 --> 01:14:30,440
She has a fear of sharp objects.

1158
01:14:30,440 --> 01:14:32,940
Daeyang Group's only daughter
is the Seo Jong Hui we know?

1159
01:14:32,940 --> 01:14:35,160
I thought I was mistaken at first, too.

1160
01:14:35,160 --> 01:14:36,530
Jong Hui...

1161
01:14:36,530 --> 01:14:37,760
Yeong Rye.

1162
01:14:37,760 --> 01:14:41,570
Jae Pil, to be honest, recently...

1163
01:14:41,570 --> 01:14:43,860
The lady asked me to bring you.

1164
01:14:43,860 --> 01:14:45,840
Hello. Nice to meet you.

1165
01:14:45,840 --> 01:14:50,730
I'll forget. But please forget my past, too.
